This paper deals with logical formalisms for spatial reasoning in AI, which suggests that cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the expressive power and computational complexity of the logics, which falls under the scope of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of topological spaces and substructures also suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) may be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions geographical information systems and constraint databases, which are relevant to cs.DB (Databases).
